What are Operators?
	
	operators are a method of packaging, deploying, and managing a Kubernetes cluster
		
		They watch the cluster state to deliver the functionality for the specific operator
		
		operator framework lets you customize features that you need
		
Cluster Operator Installation

	Installed by default or during initial cluster configuration
	
How do we manage Cluster Operators?
	
	Usually managed by the CVO (cluster version operator)
	
	OLM (operator lifecycle manager) manages installation, upgrade, and role-based access control
	
Operator Registry
	
	maintains info about ClusterServiceVersions (CSV) resources and available CUstom Resource Defintion (CRD) in the cluster.
	
	OperatorHub can add operators to a cluster
	

